            </subsection>
            <p>After downloading a distribution from the table above please proceed to verify
            your JRE.
            </p>
            <subsection name="Verifying the JRE">
                <p>Force Field X start up commands use the JRE specified by the
                    <code>JAVA_HOME</code> environment
                variable. Please verify that
                    <code>JAVA_HOME</code> references a JRE (or JDK) of version 1.6.0 or later.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>Linux</p>
                        <p>Type "
                            <code>echo $JAVA_HOME</code>" in a shell.
                        </p>
                        <p>If
                            <code>JAVA_HOME</code> is not set or the JRE version is less than 1.6.0,
                            then please follow Sun's
                            <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/6/webnotes/install/system-configurations.html" target="_blank">
                            Java installation instructions
                            </a> to install a JRE and/or set the
                            <code>JAVA_HOME</code> environment variable.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Mac OS X</p>
                        <p>Type "
                            <code>echo $JAVA_HOME</code>" in a shell. The result should look like this:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <code>/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.6.0/Home</code>
                        </p>
                        <p>If the version is less than 1.6.0, simply open "/Applications/Utilities/Java Preferences"
                        and specify version 1.6.0 (or later) to be preferred for Applications (ie. drag it to the top of the list).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Microsoft Windows</p>
                        <p>Type "
                            <code>echo %JAVA_HOME%</code>" at a DOS prompt.
                        </p>
                        <p>If
                            <code>JAVA_HOME</code> is not set or the version is less than 1.6.0, then please follow Sun's
                            <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/6/webnotes/install/system-configurations.html" target="_blank">
                            Java installation instructions
                            </a> to install a JRE. The Windows installer will set the
                            <code>JAVA_HOME</code> environment variable for you (please open a new DOS window after
                            the installation finishes to check).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>After
                    <code>JAVA_HOME</code> is verified, please read the brief installation instructions for your platform:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="download.html#linux">Linux</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="download.html#macosx">Mac OS X</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="download.html#windows">Microsoft Windows</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>

            </subsection>
            <a name="linux"/>
            <subsection name="Linux Installation Instructions">
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <p align="left">
                                <img src="images/tux.jpg" alt="LINUX" />
                            </p>
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <p>Unpack the distribution (replace VERSION based on the downloaded file):</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <code>tar -xzf ffx-VERSION-bin.tar.gz</code>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <code>unzip ffx-VERSION-bin.zip</code>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>Add the directory ffx-VERSION/bin/linux to your path. For example,
                                        if ffx is unpacked into /Users/shared/ffx-VERSION, then
                                    </p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>BASH</p>
                                            <p>export PATH="/Users/shared/ffx-VERSION/bin/linux:$PATH"</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>CSH</p>
                                            <p>setenv PATH "/Users/shared/ffx-VERSION/bin/linux:$PATH"</p>
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>To check use "
                                        <code>echo $PATH</code>" and "
                                        <code>which ffx</code>".
                                        Both the graphical
                                        <code>ffx</code> and command line
                                        compiler
                                        <code>ffxc</code> versions should now be available.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </subsection>
            <a name="macosx"/>
            <subsection name="Mac OS X Installation Instructions">
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            <p align="left">
                                <img src="images/mac.jpg" alt="MAC OS X" />
                            </p>
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <p>Unpack the distribution (replace VERSION based on the downloaded file):</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <code>tar -xzf ffx-VERSION-bin.tar.gz</code>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <code>unzip ffx-VERSION-bin.zip</code>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>Add the ffx-VERSION/bin/macosx directory to your path.
                                        For example, if ffx is unpacked into /Users/shared/ffx-VERSION, then
                                    </p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>BASH</p>
                                            <p>export PATH="/Users/shared/ffx-VERSION/bin/macosx:$PATH"</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>CSH</p>
                                            <p>setenv PATH "/Users/shared/ffx-VERSION/bin/macosx:$PATH"</p>
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>To check use "
                                        <code>echo $PATH</code>" and "
                                        <code>which ffx</code>".
                                        Both the graphical
                                        <code>ffx</code> and command line
                                        compiler
                                        <code>ffxc</code> versions should now be available.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </subsection>
